summary:
Mysterious Ways
It didn't take long for you to fall for him, his ideas about society just fascinated you. 
There was something...
body:
Mysterious Ways

It didn’t take long for you to fall for him, his ideas about society just fascinated you.

There was something that stood in between you two however, and that was his hesitation to be near you. Stain didn’t want to get too close, his job was dangerous enough without someone by his side.

Eye contact was the only intimate action he was willing to give you, rare moments that you would always remember.

It wasn’t easy, instead of kissing each other good morning, you two exchanged looks of hope at one another. It was progress, but you were willing to wait for him.

You didn’t even think of him as a villain the way media interpreted him, in your eyes he was a man willing to fight those who didn’t play fair. You had no place to judge his actions.

“Why do you continue to stay beside me?” The man asked you. 

You looked down at your hands, trying to think carefully about your answer. “I stay beside you because I believe you’re right.”

Your answer surprised him, many find his way of dealing with heroes he found fake controversial. 

“Interesting.”

“Who am I to judge?”

It was that moment that made him see you in a new light.

~~~~~~~

@sessarin

title: Req Wed: Poor Unfortunate Souls
body:
Bakugou x Kirishima

“The only way to get what you want,” Bakugou sneered, “is to become a human yourself.”

Kirishima had his magic eyes on, his bottom lip jutting out just so as he gasped, “Can you do that?”

“My dear, sweet child,” Bakugou placed a finger under Kirishima’s jaw and pulled him forward. “That’s what I do. It’s what I live for. To help unfortunate merfolk, like yourself!”

The audience jeered at him, like they always did during this part. He played the villain after all.

And when “Ariel” lost his voice, they booed Bakugou even more and cheered when “Prince Eric” finally took him down.

Bakugou hid behind the curtain when “Prince Eric” kissed the little mermaid, peeked his head out right at the end to watch Kirishima’s face as he melted against his new love. Dressed in white with the happiest smile, he exited stage left, opposite of Bakugou.

Bakugou told himself it was for the acting. Wanted to study how Kirishima delivered his lines and schooled his face. But deep down inside he knew it was the big-ass crush he had on his best friend.

He rushed to his vanity, pretended he had been taking his makeup off while Kirishima was front and center smooching the crowned prince. And when Kirishima walked in, the air left Bakugou’s chest and he forgot how to breath.

“Oh hey Bakugou, good job today!”

“Yeah whatever,” he grumped in reply, even though underneath of his little facade he was swooning.
